   "source": [
    "# 🧠 Deep Learning Journey — Chapter 1: The Single Perceptron\n",
    "\n",
    "> *"Every great deep learning model you'll ever build starts here — with a single neuron."*\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 📌 What is a Perceptron?\n",
    "\n",
    "A **Perceptron** is the simplest form of a neural network — a single artificial neuron. It was invented by **Frank Rosenblatt in 1958** and is the foundation of all modern deep learning.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🔢 Mathematical Formula\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\hat{y} = \\text{step}\\left(\\sum_{i=1}^{n} w_i x_i + b\\right)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where:\n",
    "- $x_i$ = input features\n",
    "- $w_i$ = learned weights\n",
    "- $b$ = bias\n",
    "- $\\text{step}(z) = 1$ if $z \\geq 0$, else $0$\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🎯 Task: Predict Student Placement\n",
    "We'll use a **Single Perceptron** (from scratch + sklearn) to predict whether a student gets **placed (1) or not (0)** based on academic features.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📚 Step 1: Import Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
